\section*{Symptoms}
-Vary widely in severity but almost always occur shortly after birth.
-The time of presentation depends on amount of intestine involved as long segment -present early.
1-Delayed passage of meconium
2-Chronic or intermittent constipation with diarrhea
3-.Passage of flatus and stool requires great effort, and the stools are small in caliber.
